cs.IT, cs.GT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MA. 

The paper deals with resource allocation problems and communication between a centralized controller and distributed users. This suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories, including Information Theory (cs.IT), Game Theory (cs.GT), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Systems and Control (cs.SY), and Multiagent Systems (cs.MA). However, the focus on communication and quantization techniques suggests that cs.IT and cs.NI are the most likely sub-categories. The use of dynamic programming and optimization techniques also supports the possibility of cs.MA and cs.SY.
